how to create hierachy from one column. Example we have level column which contains values 1,2,3,4 (level)
and when you want to have dropdown you need to divide them into columns and create hierachy like in date table
if in column level is value 4 in new column level 3 will be value 3, in level 2 will be value 2...
so depending from number of levels we will need same amount of columns
first we need to create for lowest level column : L5 Activity ONB = L5 Activity Name = if('martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityLevel]=5,'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],BLANK())
then level 4 : L4 Activity Name = 
IF(
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityLevel] = 4,
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
    IF(
        ISBLANK('martCorp dimActivity_V'[L5 Activity ONB]),
        BLANK(),
        LOOKUPVALUE(
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityONB],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[L5 Activity ONB]
        )
    )
)
then level 3: L3 Activity Name = 
IF(
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityLevel] = 3,
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
    IF(
        ISBLANK('martCorp dimActivity_V'[L4 Activity ONB]),
        BLANK(),
        LOOKUPVALUE(
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityONB],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[L4 Activity ONB]
        )
    )
)
and level 1 : L1 Activity Name = 
IF(
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityLevel] = 1,
    'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
    IF(
        ISBLANK('martCorp dimActivity_V'[L2 Activity ONB]),
        BLANK(),
        LOOKUPVALUE(
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityName],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[ActivityONB],
            'martCorp dimActivity_V'[L2 Activity ONB]
        )
    )
)
